SIMPLE: immiscible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immiscible
<hw>Im*mis"ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>miscible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>immiscible</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not capable of being
mixed or mingled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A chaos of <qex>immiscible</qex> and conflicting particles.</q>
<rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Not miscible; forming two distinct phases when mixed at some
concentration; -- of two liquids; <as>as, water and gasoline are
<ex>immiscible</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immission</ent>⟦br⟧
